body:
Post the names of all the files in your WIP folder, regardless of how ridiculous and non-descriptive.

Oh boy, here we go *cracks knuckles*

Game of Thrones /ASOIAF

- “Crazy Stupid Love”: Joffrey/Viserys modern AU

- “Fake it till you make it”: Joffrey/Viserys modern AU, fake dating trope

- “Soulmarked”: Victarion Greyjoy/Talbert Serry modern AU, Soulmate AU

- “Pretend I’m here”: Joffrey/Viserys modern AU, long distance relationship

- “SilverScale”: Joffrey/Viserys modern au, meeting in a club

- “JV Idea”: Joffrey/Viserys modern au, social media fame au

- “Meeting the Targs”: Dunk/Egg modern au, meeting the family

- “Storm’s End Power Out”: all the Baratheon kids locked in at the mansion, modern au

- “Ice skater/Hockey player”: Gendrya modern au

- “Little Steff’s babysitting adventures”: modern au, Gendrya’s son is babysat by various friends/family, more like a oneshot collection

- “Remember, lousy lizard!”: Joffrey/Viserys modern au, Viserys wakes up with amnesia

Haikyuu!!

- “Eggplant Party”: chatfic with the first years, I need to get back to that one actually

- “Mage/Sniper AU”: I have no idea how to describe this

- “Kei’s Anatomy”: KuroTsuki doctor AU, A/B/O where Alphas are at an disadvantage in society

Kuroko no Basuke

- “Heavy is the Head”: NijiHai, medieval A/B/O that I should get back to as well lmao

- “Single Dad Kise”: AoKise friends to lovers, single parent AU

- “Emergency Contact”: NijiHai, future AU, Nijimura picking up Haizaki at the hospital after an accident

- “Kuroko’s Café”: KagaKuro coffee shop AU, where the GoM run a café and live together

- “Myak”: MayuAka after the match against Jabberwock

- “HQ Royal AU”: medieval AU, A/B/O

- “Rich boy Haizaki”: NijiHai, Haizaki comes from money, meeting the family

Harry Potter

- “Jeddy’s Stag”: exactly what the title says

- “Whoops”: (that title’s a prime example of placeholder) Adult Scorpius and Albus find out their fathers are dating

- “HP Magic Uni AU”: basically a college AU

- “Idk what this is”: Grudders’ daughter gets her Hogwarts letter

- “Idk what this is too”: Ludo Bagman/Gilderoy Lockhart trying to parent

- “Tombrax”: Draco finds out that his grandfather and the Dark Lord had something going on in Hogwarts

- “Idek anymore”: Goyle and Dudley get introduced at Drarry’s wedding

Hetalia

- “¡Baila para mí!”: NethSpa human AU, night club x business AU

- “Summer sweethearts”: human AU, boarding school AU, François is on a matchmaking mission during summer break

- “NethSpa”: Neth drunk-calls Spain

- “ScotFra”: human AU, François meets his soulmate at USUK’s wedding and panics

Marvel

- “Soulmate AU”: AU where your soulmate’s initials show up on your wrist

- “My somehow brother’s big, fat Avenger wedding”: Interweb wedding, Harley planning it

- “Idk yet”: a giant AU idea (A/B/O)

• “Maternity Leave”: Steve applying for leave with Tony

• “Woolang”: Scott telling Cassie she’ll be a sister

• “Morgan’s birth”: Pepperony, self-explanatory

• “Souson MP”: Jackdaniels/Souson, Jack wants to get rid of the baby bc the 40s aren’t really tolerant and stuff

• “PM: Tony’s retirement”: basically a press notice

• “N”: Tony and Bruce help Steve with his first kid’s birth (based on the idea that Steve went under the ice while pregnant)

• “Brock’s discovery”: Rumrollins/Hydra Husbands, Brock’s having a crisis at the prospect of having a family with Jack

- “SamScott”: Neighbour AU, no powers

K-Project

- “Post-Canon Sukanna”: title says it all

- “Inferno’s melody”: medieval AU, A/B/O

BBC Sherlock

- “No Rest for the wicked”: Soulmate AU, Msytrade with side Sheriarty, German, cancelled

- “Watch me fall apart”: Sheriarty prequel to NRFTW, won’t be ever finished

DC/Arrowverse

- “TimeHex”: Rip’s clandestinely ommunicating through time with Jonah and the team thinks he’s up to no good

- “Not so bad”: the Legends get catapulted onto an alternate earth, a device to get them back is at Ray’s doppelganger’s house, a house with a doorbell reading “Rory-Palmer”

- “Earth-37”: Barrison, the first earth where Barry and Iris aren’t married — Barry and Harry are

A:tlA / LoK

- “Lieumon Ghost”: the Lieutenant is haunted by Amon’s ghost

- “Post-Canon Weilin”: Wei and Bolin bond in Zhaofu

- “Modern LoK Wuko”: modern AU, Mako’s a cop on paternity leave, Wu can’t really take time off as a king, and Mako’s slowly losing his mind

summary: My friend doesn't watch Game of Thrones and I asked her to describe the characters:
body:
My friend doesn’t watch Game of Thrones and I asked her to describe the characters:

Arya: Baby girl, baby

Sansa: She has nice hair and relationship issues

Jon: Apparently, he knows nothing

Bran: Tiny

Rickon: The zig-zag man

Robb: Dead?

Theon: Robin Hood

Daenerys: The one that’s nice to look at

Viserys: Legolas

Khal Drogo: He looks like Aquaman

Jorah: He looks like a very tired dad

Cersei: That’s the bitch, right?

Jaime: Handicapped twin of the bitch

Tyrion: Oh, that’s Peter Dinklage

Joffrey: Dickhead

The Hound: Two-face but with Thor’s hair

Margaery: She’s ginger and pretty, I like her

Melisandre: Pretty scary witch lady

Stannis: He’s got that flaming sword, right?

Shireen: Tiny baby girl with velociraptor skin

Ygritte: Angry Merida that knows more than Jon Snow

Ramsay: The dude that’s pretty and scary

Night King: Elsa with freezer burn

summary: Things I’m confused by this week: why is everyone acting like this script article from VF contains anything new? Nothing in it...
body: Things I’m confused by this week: why is everyone acting like this script article from VF contains anything new? Nothing in it is new. We knew all of this from the season 7 leaks from September 2016 (kill me now) and from the hack the following summer. Nothing has changed or is new from this article and yet people are all excitable? It’s weird that this is ~~~ a thing~~~ yet again. There’s straws to be grasped, I guess? We really need new content, thanks for nothing HBO.
